This paper discusses the design and implementation of distributed systems, which is a topic that falls under the category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). The paper also discusses data management and consistency models, which are topics that fall under the categories of Databases (cs.DB) and Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the practical applications of CRDTs, which is a topic that falls under the category of Software Engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the paper discusses the design and implementation of CRDTs themselves, which is a topic that falls under the category of Programming Languages (cs.PL).
